The paper proposes a novel model based on Artificial Neural Networks to answer questions with multiple answers by exploiting multiple facts retrieved from a knowledge base. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the model is evaluated on the factoid Question Answering and top-n recommendation tasks of the bAbI Movie Dialog dataset, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Neural Networks (cs.NE).
